{"word":"ἀμφιάνακτες","slug":"ἀμφιάνακτες","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n5708\" key=\"a)mfia/naktes\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ἀμφιάνακτες</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ων</itype>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">οἱ</gen>, nickname of <sense id=\"n5708.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">dithyrambic poets,</tr_> because their odes often began thus—<foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἀμφί μοι αὖθις ἄνακτα</foreign> or <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἀμφί μοι αὖτε, ἄναξ,</foreign> Sch.<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg003.perseus-grc1:595\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ar.\">Ar.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Nu.\">Nu.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">595</biblScope></bibl>. <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ἀμφιανακτίζω</orth>, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">sing dithyrambic hymns,</tr_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0434.tlg001:67\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Cratin.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">67</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg012:59\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ar.\">Ar.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Fr.\">Fr.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">59</biblScope></bibl>, cf. foreg.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}